1. d4 Nf6 2. c4 g6 3. Nc3 Bg7 4. e4 d6 5. Nf3 O-O 6. Be2 e5 7. O-O Nc6 8. d5
Ne7 9. Ne1 Nd7 10. Be3 f5 11. f3 f4 12. Bf2 g5 13. Nd3 Ng6 14. c5 Nf6 15. Rc1
Rf7 16. Qc2 $5 ({Usual is} 16. cxd6 cxd6 17. Nb5) 16... g4 $1 17. fxg4 $5 Bxg4
18. Bf3 Bf8 19. cxd6 cxd6 20. Nb5 $2 Rg7 $2 {They miss a tactical point.} (
20... Bxf3 21. gxf3 Qd7 22. a4 a6 {wins for Black.}) 21. Bxg4 Nxg4 22. Nc7 Rc8
23. Ne6 $1 Rxc2 24. Nxd8 Rgc7 25. Bxa7 {White has an extra pawn, but Black
attacks.} Nf6 26. Bb6 $5 Rxc1 27. Rxc1 Rxc1+ 28. Nxc1 Nxe4 29. Nxb7 Ne7 $1 30.
a4 Nxd5 31. a5 $1 Nxb6 $2 (31... Be7 32. Bd8 Bxd8 33. Nxd8 Nc7 {keeps the
equality.}) 32. axb6 {The doubled pawns become strong.} d5 33. Nd3 Nd6 $5 34.
Nd8 e4 $5 35. Nxf4 Nc4 36. b7 Bd6 37. Nxd5 Ne5 38. b4 Kf8 39. b5 Ke8 40. Nc6
Nd7 41. Ndb4 {Pomar has two extra pawns and will queen soon.} 1-0

